SE_WVUvsPitt_TT-00352.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 2 May 2026 20:42:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59072</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Shut Out Kansas State</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/1/baseball-mountaineers-shut-out-kansas-state</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/1/baseball-mountaineers-shut-out-kansas-state</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Maxx Yehl" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/1/DSC02618-2.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Behind redshirt junior Maxx Yehl and graduate student Ian Korn, the No. 18 West Virginia University baseball team shut out Kansas State, 7-0, Friday evening at Kendrick Family Ballpark. The Mountaineers improve to 29-12 and 14-8 in the Big 12 while the Wildcats fall to 26-20 and 9-13 in conference play.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/1/DSC02618-2.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/1/DSC02618-2.jpg"><media:title>Maxx Yehl</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/1/DSC02618-2.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 1 May 2026 23:41:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59071</s:story_id></item><item><title>Hodge Announces Signing of Amadou Seini</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/1/mens-basketball-hodge-announces-signing-of-amadou-seini</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/1/mens-basketball-hodge-announces-signing-of-amadou-seini</guid><category>Men's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Freshman Amadou Seini signs with the M